      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the butter, caster sugar, and dark brown sugar together until fluffy. Beat in the egg and vanilla. Stir in the almond flour, rice flour, bicarbonate of soda, and salt until a soft dough forms. Fold in the chocolate chips. Chill the dough for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Line two baking trays with baking paper. Scoop tablespoon-sized balls of dough onto the trays, spacing them at least 5 cm apart. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the edges are set and lightly golden. The centres will look underdone; leave to cool on the tray for 5 minutes before transferring to a rack. They firm as they cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
